JUST a quick note, you do NOT have to do the cooking mushrooms for 3 hours the Dr. Ray Peat way thing. You can just cook them normally and it's 100% ok. It comes from some studies where extract from mushrooms cooked 3 hours didn't lose any of its benefits and was fully effective.

If you want to use them as a carrot salad type endotoxin cleanse thing daily for years then maybe cooking them longer will make more sense, but if you're just having a mushroom delicious meal once or twice per week you can just use any recipe without worrying much. Cheers bros.

The good nutrients in mushrooms are very heat-stable and are not lost in cooking. BUT if you're not in poor health or don't have some sort of liver issue cooking mushrooms the regular way is ok as long as you're not eating industrial amounts of them every single day.
